ng several of the top applications listed in Google Play and the App Store including [[Acompli]],<ref>{{cite web|last=Molina|first=Brett|title=Microsoft acquires email app Acompli |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/tech/2014/12/01/microsoft-acompli/19739113/|website=[[USA Today]]|date=1 December 2014}}</ref> [[Sunrise Calendar]],<ref>{{cite web|last=Warren|first=Tom|title=Microsoft acquires Sunrise, the best calendar app for iOS and Android |url=https://www.theverge.com/2015/2/11/7984603/microsoft-sunrise-acquisition-official|website=[[The Verge]]|publisher=[[Vox Media]]|date=11 February 2015}}</ref> Datazen,<ref>{{cite web|last=Foley|first=Mary Jo|title=Microsoft acquires mobile BI vendor Datazen. Microsoft has purchased cross-platform, mobile business-intelligence vendor Datazen Software, a Toronto-based company, for an undisclosed amount |url=http://www.zdnet.com/article/microsoft-acquires-mobile-bi-vendor-datazen/|website=[[ZDNt]] |publisher=[[CBS Interactive]] |date=14 April 2015}}</ref> [[Wunderlist]],<ref>{{cite web|last=Novet|first=Jordan|title=Microsoft confirms acquisition of Wunderlist app maker 6Wunderkinder |url=https://venturebeat.com/2015/06/02/microsoft-confirms-its-acquisition-of-wunderlist-app-maker-6wunderkinder/|website=Venturebeat|date=2 June 2015}}</ref> Echo Notification Lockscreen,<ref>{{cite web|last=Frank|first=Blair Hanley|title=Microsoft buys popular Android lock-screen app maker. The acquisition means Microsoft now owns two Android lock-screen apps|url=http://www.pcworld.com/article/2983581/microsoft-buys-popular-android-lock-screen-app-maker.html|website=PC World|date=11 September 2015}}</ref> and [[MileIQ]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Kim|first=Eugene|title=Microsoft just bought a startup that can automatically track how far you drive|url=http://uk.businessinsider.com/microsoft-acquires-mobile-data-labs-2015-11?r=US&IR=T|website=Business Insider|date=5 November 2015}}</ref>\n\n== Applications and Web Services ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n