sts.\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!width=14%|Inmate Name\n!width=10%|Register Number\n!width=23%|Status\n!width=53%|Details\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[Schaeffer Cox|Francis Schaeffer Cox]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| [http://www.bop.gov/iloc2/InmateFinderServlet?Transaction=IDSearch&needingMoreList=false&IDType=IRN&IDNumber=16179-006&x=73&y=19 16179-006]\n| Now at [[Federal Correctional Institution, Terre Haute|FCI Terre Haute]]\n| Leader of the Alaska Peacekeepers Militia; convicted in 2012 of murder [[conspiracy (crime)|conspiracy]] for plotting the murders of judges and law enforcement agents; two co-defendants were also sentenced to prison.<ref>{{cite news|last=Rosen |first=Yereth |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2013/01/09/us-usa-militia-alaska-idUSBRE90803H20130109 |title=Alaska militia leader sentenced to nearly 26 years in prison |publisher=Reuters |date=2013-01-09 |accessdate=2014-03-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.justice.gov/usao/ak/news/2012/June_2012/Francis%20Schaeffer%20Cox.html |title=USDOJ: US Attorney's Office - Alaska |publisher=Justice.gov |date=June 2012 |accessdate=2014-03-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140315130353/http://www.justice.gov/usao/ak/news/2012/June_2012/Francis%20Schaeffer%20Cox.html |archive-date=March 15, 2014 |url-status=dead |df=mdy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.atf.gov/press/releases/2013/01/010913-sea-fairbanks-residents-sentenced-for-conspiracy-to-murder-public-officials-and-weapons-violations.html |title=Fairbanks Residents Sentenced for Conspiracy to Murder Public Officials and Weapons Violations &#124; ATF |publisher=Atf.gov |date=2013-01-09 |accessdate=2014-03-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140315113423/http://www.atf.gov/press/releases/2013/01/010913-sea-fairbanks-residents-sentenced-for-conspiracy-to-murder-public-officials-and-weapons-violations.html |archive-date=March 15, 2014 |url-status=dead |df=mdy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|auth