er persons outside the US for attempting to join [[Al-Shabaab (militant group)|Al Shabaab]], a terrorist group based in Somalia; co-conspirator Mohamed Alessa was sentenced to 22 years.<ref name=\"autogenerated1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.nj.com/news/jjournal/index.ssf?/base/news-4/1276152059131710.xml&coll=3 |title=Lawyers for terror suspects from North Bergen and Elmwood Park will ask federal judge to allow bail at hearing today in Newark |publisher=NJ.com |date= |accessdate=June 10, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.justice.gov/usao/nj/Press/files/Alessa,%20Mohamed%20et.%20al.%20News%20Release.html |title=USDOJ: US Attorney's Office - District of New Jersey |publisher=Justice.gov |accessdate=2014-03-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130713052618/http://www.justice.gov/usao/nj/Press/files/Alessa,%20Mohamed%20et.%20al.%20News%20Release.html# |archive-date=July 13, 2013 |url-status=dead |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[Richard Scutari]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| [http://www.bop.gov/iloc2/InmateFinderServlet?Transaction=IDSearch&needingMoreList=false&IDType=IRN&IDNumber=34840-080&x=91&y=22 34840-080]\n| Serving a 60-year sentence\n| Former member of the white supremacist group [[The Order (white supremacist group)|The Order]]. Convicted in 1987 of conspiracy, racketeering, and robbery. Sentenced to 60 years in prison. Transferred to [[Federal Correctional Institution, Mendota]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[October 2018 United States mail bombing attempts|Cesar Altieri Sayoc]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| [http://www.bop.gov/iloc2/InmateFinderServlet?Transaction=IDSearch&needingMoreList=false&IDType=IRN&IDNumber=34840-080&x=91&y=22 17781-104]\n| Serving a 20-year sentence, scheduled for release on November 10, 2035\n|Plead guilty to mailing explosive devices to critics of [[US President Donald Trump]]. These included leading [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic Party]] politicians such as former U.S. President [[Barack Obama]], former U.S. Vice President [[Joe Biden]], and former U.S. Secretary of State [[Hillary Clinton]]. One package was addressed only to [[CNN]] and sent to its [[CNN Center|world headquarters]]. \n|}\n\n===Organized crime figures===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!width=14%|Inmate Name\n!width=8%|Register Number\n!width=5%|Photo\n!width=27%|Status\n!width=51%|Details\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{sortname|John|Gotti}}\u2020\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| [http://www.bop.gov/iloc2/InmateFinderServlet?Transaction=IDSearch&needingMoreList=false&IDType=IRN&IDNumber=18261-053&x=88&y=19 18261-053]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[File:John Gotti.jpg|80px]]\n| Died in 2002 while serving a life sentence.\n| Boss of the [[Gambino Crime Family]] in New York City from 1985 to 1992; convicted of murder, [[Conspiracy (crime)|murder conspiracy]], [[loansharking]], [[illegal gambling]], [[obstruction of justice]], [[bribery]], and [[tax evasion]] in 1992.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{sortname|William|Daddano, Sr.}}\u2020\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| Unlisted\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \n| Died in 1975 while serving a 15-year sentence.\n| Top [[loan shark]] and [[extortion|enforcer]] for the [[Chicago Outfit|Chicago Mafia]]; convicted in 1964 of [[Conspiracy (crime)|conspiracy]] to commit bank robbery.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://americanmafia.com/Feature_Articles_233.html |title=Feature Articles 233 |publisher=AmericanMafia.com |date=1969-08-27 |accessdate=2014-03-15}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| {{sortname|Viktor|Bout}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| [http://www.bop.gov/iloc2/InmateFinderServlet?Transaction=IDSearch&needingMoreList=false&IDType=IRN&IDNumber=91641-054&x=87&y=20 91641-054]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[File:Viktor Bout Extradited to US.jpg|80px]]\n| Serving a 25-year sentence; scheduled for release in 2030.\n| Russian [[arms trafficking|arms dealer]]; convicted in 2011 of 